@startuml
title Linux kernel boot to virtio-gpu / DRM registration

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam monochrome true
autonumber

participant "bootloader\n(QEMU BIOS -> bzImage)" as Bootloader
participant "start_kernel()\n(init/main.c)" as StartKernel
participant "rest_init()\n(init/main.c)" as RestInit
participant "kernel_init()\n(init/main.c)" as KernelInit
participant "do_basic_setup()\n(init/main.c)" as BasicSetup
participant "do_initcalls()\n(init/main.c)" as Initcalls
participant "PCI core\n(drivers/pci/)" as PCICore
participant "virtio_gpu_driver_init()\n(drivers/gpu/drm/virtio/virtgpu_drv.c)" as VirtioGPUInit
participant "register_virtio_driver()\n(drivers/virtio/virtio.c)" as RegisterVirtio
participant "virtio_gpu_probe()\n(drivers/gpu/drm/virtio/virtgpu_drv.c)" as VirtioGPUProbe
participant "drm_dev_alloc()\n(drivers/gpu/drm/drm_drv.c)" as DRMDevAlloc
participant "virtio_gpu_init()\n(drivers/gpu/drm/virtio/virtgpu.c)" as VirtioGPUInitHw
participant "virtio_gpu_modeset_init()\n(drivers/gpu/drm/virtio/virtgpu_display.c)" as VirtioGPUModesetInit
participant "drmm_mode_config_init()\n(drivers/gpu/drm/drm_drv.c)" as DRMModeConfigInit
participant "vgdev_output_init()\n(drivers/gpu/drm/virtio/virtgpu_display.c)" as VGDevOutputInit
participant "drm_crtc_init_with_planes()\n(drivers/gpu/drm/drm_crtc.c)" as DRMCRTCInit
participant "drm_connector_init()\n(drivers/gpu/drm/drm_connector.c)" as DRMConnectorInit
participant "drm_simple_encoder_init()\n(drivers/gpu/drm/drm_simple_kms_helper.c)" as DRMEncoderInit
participant "drm_dev_register()\n(drivers/gpu/drm/drm_drv.c)" as DRMRegister
participant "drm_client_setup()\n(drivers/gpu/drm/clients/drm_client_setup.c)" as DRMClientSetup
participant "console_init()/printk\n(kernel/printk)" as Console
participant "init\n(/sbin/init or /bin/sh)" as InitProcess
participant "modetest\n(user space)" as Modetest

== Boot starts ==
Bootloader -> StartKernel : jump into Linux kernel entry
note right of StartKernel
We skip early arch setup:
decompress, paging, CPU bring-up,
and other low-level init.
end note

StartKernel -> Console : printk/log buffer ready\nearly boot messages start
StartKernel -> RestInit : rest_init()
RestInit -> KernelInit : kernel_init()
KernelInit -> BasicSetup : do_basic_setup()
BasicSetup -> Initcalls : do_initcalls()

== Driver init phase ==
Initcalls -> PCICore : PCI bus init / device discovery
Initcalls -> VirtioGPUInit : module_init(virtio_gpu_driver_init)
VirtioGPUInit -> RegisterVirtio : register_virtio_driver(&virtio_gpu_driver)
RegisterVirtio -> VirtioGPUProbe : match VIRTIO_ID_GPU\ninvoke .probe = virtio_gpu_probe()
VirtioGPUProbe -> DRMDevAlloc : drm_dev_alloc(&driver, parent)
DRMDevAlloc --> VirtioGPUProbe : struct drm_device *dev
VirtioGPUProbe -> VirtioGPUInitHw : virtio_gpu_init(vdev, dev)
VirtioGPUInitHw -> VirtioGPUModesetInit : virtio_gpu_modeset_init(vgdev)
VirtioGPUModesetInit -> DRMModeConfigInit : drmm_mode_config_init(vgdev->ddev)
DRMModeConfigInit --> VirtioGPUModesetInit : mode_config ready
loop for each scanout
  VirtioGPUModesetInit -> VGDevOutputInit : vgdev_output_init(vgdev, index)
  VGDevOutputInit -> DRMCRTCInit : drm_crtc_init_with_planes()
  VGDevOutputInit -> DRMConnectorInit : drm_connector_init()
  VGDevOutputInit -> DRMEncoderInit : drm_simple_encoder_init()
end
VirtioGPUModesetInit --> VirtioGPUInitHw : CRTC / connector / encoder registered
VirtioGPUInitHw --> VirtioGPUProbe : scanouts / buffers / DRM state ready
VirtioGPUProbe -> DRMRegister : drm_dev_register(dev, 0)
DRMRegister --> VirtioGPUProbe : /dev/dri/card0 created
VirtioGPUProbe -> DRMClientSetup : drm_client_setup(vdev->priv, NULL)
DRMClientSetup --> VirtioGPUProbe : fbdev/log client attach if enabled

note right of VirtioGPUProbe
This is the important point:
the DRM device becomes available
during kernel driver initialization,
not later in user space.

In virtio_gpu_probe():
1. drm_dev_alloc()
2. virtio_gpu_init()
   -> virtio_gpu_modeset_init()
      -> drmm_mode_config_init()
      -> vgdev_output_init()
         -> drm_crtc_init_with_planes()
         -> drm_connector_init()
         -> drm_simple_encoder_init()
3. drm_dev_register()
4. drm_client_setup()
end note

== Userspace starts ==
KernelInit -> InitProcess : spawn PID 1
InitProcess -> Console : buildroot login:\n(or /bin/sh if init=/bin/sh)
InitProcess -> Modetest : user launches modetest
Modetest -> DRMRegister : opens /dev/dri/card0\nand uses DRM ioctls

note over Modetest
For learning:
1. boot to kernel init
2. PCI/virtio GPU probe
3. DRM registration
4. user space opens /dev/dri/card0
5. modetest issues KMS ioctls
end note

@enduml
